# Random Map Generation

This is a python/pygame implementation of the wave function collapse algorithm, inspired by what is done on [CodingTrain/Wave-Function-Collapse](https://github.com/CodingTrain/Wave-Function-Collapse). (written on p5)


![Demo](https://github.com/sidalihmdn/wave-function-collapse/blob/develop/demo.gif)

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.11
- Pygame

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/sidalihmdn/wave-function-collapse.git
    cd wave-function-collapse
    ```

2. Install the dependencies:
    ```sh
    pipenv install
    ```

## Usage

1. Run the main script:
    ```sh
    pipenv run python main.py
    ```

2. Use the space bar to collapse the grid.

## Project Structure

- [consts.py](http://_vscodecontentref_/1): Defines constants used in the project.
- [grid.py](http://_vscodecontentref_/2): Contains the classes , , and  to manage the grid and tiles.
- [main.py](http://_vscodecontentref_/6): Main script to run the project.
- [tiles](http://_vscodecontentref_/7): Contains the tile images.



